-- Grammy Awards Draw 39 Million TV Viewers
-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 2012-02-13T16:57:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/grammy-awards-draw-39-million-tv-viewers.html
The Grammy awards telecast on CBS
last night attracted 39 million viewers, the second-largest ever
for the annual music-industry show, according to preliminary
data from the network.  The program, which included a tribute to Whitney Houston,
who died Feb. 11, was seen in 21.8 percent of the 114.7 million
U.S. TV households. The most-watched Grammy telecast was the
1984 show, which drew 51.7 million viewers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Golum at 
 rgolum@bloomberg.net  